40|$|This {{thesis is}} dealing with the {{cohesion}} <b>of</b> the <b>tax</b> and accounting system and shows how this cohesion can negatively affect accounting. In order to reduce the <b>tax</b> base <b>of</b> the corporate income tax, taxpayers resort to tax evasion, which ultimately leads to the restriction of informative ability of accounting. The thesis introduces some formats <b>of</b> <b>tax</b> evasion, including practical examples. Listed further are tax deductible and non-deductible expenses. It creates a space for manipulating the financial results on operations, which is the starting point for determining the tax base on corporate income. The closing section contains a modification of financial results on operations for the tax base and calculation <b>of</b> <b>tax</b> <b>payable</b> on corporate income...|$|R
